-- Germany, Ghana Advance at World Cup; Australia, Serbia Eliminated
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-23T20:45:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/germany-ghana-advance-to-world-cup-round-of-16-australia-serbia-are-out.html

          
          
             Germany and Ghana advanced to the
round of 16 at the World Cup from Group D, while Australia and
Serbia were eliminated.  
 Germany beat Ghana 1-0 to win the group with six points.
Ghana and Australia, which defeated Serbia 2-1, finished with
four points, Ghana taking the second qualifying place on a
superior goal difference. Serbia was last with three points.  
 Ghana will face the U.S. next on June 26, with Germany
meeting England the following day. The U.S. beat Algeria 1-0
earlier today to win Group C, and England was second after
beating Slovenia 1-0.  
 Mesut Ozil scored in the 60th minute in Johannesburg to
give Germany the victory.  Tim Cahill  and Brett Holman had goals
four minutes apart in the second half for Australia in
Nelspruit.  
